	   <tr><td colspan=2>Succeeded in my quest for my Trueshot Longbow today.&nbsp;&nbsp;Was with my 12th level Woodelf Ranger - Hytreker: Dex 80; Wis 100; Int 75; Cha 75; Master Fletcher 163. <br><br>I want to thank all the useful posts.  I spent the first bit just collecting items and amassed enough materials for 17 attempts.  During that time I leveled from 8th to 12th as did the majority of my hunting group (took about three 5hr days).<br><br>My friends then pooled together all their resources giving me approximately 175pp to work with.  Using that and about an hour or so I was able to boost my fletching from 0 to it's current level (163) and viola! On my third attempt I succeeded in becoming the proud owner of my very own Trueshot Longbow!  <br><br>Couple things to keep in mind:<br><br>The Dwarven wire and micro servos are NO DROP items, so make sure your buddy gives you the tumpy tonics. (D'oh!)<br><br>The Treant Bowstaves are LORE ITEMS so get used to sitting at the feet of the guild master and getting yer staves one at a time.<br><br>I highly recommend hunting rogue clockworks (for your micro servos) in the Steamfont Zone near the Minotaur camp entrance.  They were there in abundance and around 9th just about everything was conning blue to me with very few agroes. Be aware that they will swarm you if there is another clockwork nearby.  Also be wary of the Kobold Missionary and the occasional Red Mino runnin through.<br><br>Other than that... start young and have fun and get the experience as you complete your quest.  And YES! the shots are much sweeter coming from your own handiwork!<br><br>Thanks go out especially to Xhuli, Sanad, Carpledex and Alchemancer on the Veeshan server for helping me through the quest.  Now we are off to find a better piercing weapon for Carple!<br>&nbsp;<br>Wulfgarin &lt;CotGW&gt;<br>Barbarian Shaman (Veeshan)<br>"Every Wulf has fleas... I have but to scratch"</td></tr>
