<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100213042563149></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100213042563149><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=2672&mid=100213042563149>RE: first part of trueshot qst</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=2672&mid=100213042563149#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=74789><span id= >mjfruits</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>8 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Oct 3rd 1:33 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Put the following into the Material Bag that Maesyn gives you:<br><br>1 Spiderling Silk<br>1 Dwarven Wire<br>1 Micro Servo<br>1 Treant Wood (you get these from Jyle Windshots in West Freeport)<br><br>Then click on combine. Now the bag will be replaced with another bag, which you give back to Maesyn, who then gives you the Treantwood Bowstave. Once you get the the Bowstave, put the Bowstave, 1 Dwarven Wire, 1 Micro Servo, and a Planning Tool into your Fletching Kit and click on Combine. If you close your eyes, cross your fingers and rub your rabbit's foot long enough, you'll get a nice Trueshot Bow on the end of your cursor :-)<br><br>Fruits &lt;15 Ranger Woodelf&gt;<br>Eriollisi Marr server<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
